                                                LOOPS

While Loops -> counting a specific number of iterations.
For Loops -> iterating over all elements of a container.

TOPIC: While loop vs. For loop

    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
                      while loop                    |                   for loop
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
        i = 0                                       |
        while i < 100:                              |   for i in range (100):
            | Loop body statements |                |       | Loop body statements |
            i += 1                                  |
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    + must assign variable i before loop            | + less likely to become stuck in infinite
    + must increment variable at the end            | + use when number of iterations is computable
    + use when number of iterations is not          |   before entering loop.
      computable, as looping until user enters a    | + use when accessing the elements of a container,
      particular character.                         |   as when adding 1 to every element.
.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: WHILE LOOPS

    Syntax:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    while |expression|:
        | Loop Body |

    | Executional expressions after loop has been exited |
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    Vocabs:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    + Sentinel Value: value that causes a loop to end.
    + Infinite loop: loop never stops running because condition is always True.
        - include greater than or less than along with equality in loop expression.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: FOR LOOPS

    Syntax:
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    for variable in container:
        | Loop Body |

    | Executional statements after the for loop is complete |
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

    LIST: Outputting using for loop                 | Output:
                                                    |
        fruits_list = ["apple", "banana", "cherry"] |   apple
        for fruit in fruits_list:                   |   banana
            print(fruit)                            |   chery

    + fruit -> variable to hold element in the list.
    + fruits_list -> list container

    LIST: Searching using for loop                  | Output:
                                                    |
        my_list = [5, 6, 7]                         |   Found element 5
        for x in my_list:                           |
            if x == 5:                              |
                print("Found element 5")            |

    STRINGS: Outputting each character in a string  | Output:
                                                    |
        my_str = "Yes"                              |   Y
        for char in my_str:                         |   E
            print(char)                             |   S

    DICTIONARY: Iterating over dict using for loop  | Output:
                                                    |
        channels = {                                |   MTV is on channel 35
            "MTV": 35,                              |   CNN is on channel 28
            "CNN": 28,                              |   NBC is on channel 4
            "NBC": 4                                |
        }                                           |

        for channel_name in channels:
            print(f"{channel_name} is on channel {channels[channel_name]}")

    DICTIONARY: Outputting in REVERSE               | Output:
                                                    |
        names = [                                   |   Armando | Lena | Aidan | Norah
            "Armando",                              |
            "Lena",                                 |   Norah | Aidan | Lena | Armando
            "Aidan",                                |
            "Norah"                                 |   + Output a list in reverse using
        ]                                           |   reversed() function.
        # printing normal                           |
        for name in names:                          |   + adding (end= " ") will cause the line
            print(name, "|", end=" ")               |   to end with a space instead of new line.
                                                    |
        # printing reversed                         |
        for name in reversed(names):                |
            print(name, "|", end= " ")              |

