TOPIC: range() function (for loops)

    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Notes:
        + Ranges represent an arithmetic progression: some sequence of integers with a start, end, and
          step between integers.
        + The range type is a sequence type like lists and tuples but is immutable.
        + In general, range objects are only used as part of a for loop statements.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


    Range                  | Generated Sequence         | Explanation
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (5)              | 0 1 2 3 4                  | Every int from 0 to 4
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (0, 5)           | 0 1 2 3 4                  | Every int from 0 to 4
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (3, 7)           | 3 4 5 6                    | Every integer from 3 to 6 before 7
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (10, 13)         | 10 11 12                   | Every int from 10 to 12 before 13
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (0, 5, 1)        | 0 1 2 3 4                  | Every 1 integer from 0 to 4
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (0, 5, 2)        | 0 2 4                      | Every 2nd int from 0 to 4
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (5, 0 , -1)      | 5 4 3 2 1                  | Every 1 int from 5 to 1
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    range (5, 0 , -2)      | 5 3 1                      | Every 2nd int from 5 to 1
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: NESTED LOOPS

   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
   Notes:
    + Determining how many times a nested loop will iterate by multiplying outer and inner loop.
   -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

   While loops:
    + Outer loops controls the "rows", Inner lops run through "columns" for each row.

   row = 1                                  | Output:
   while row <= 3:                          |
       col = 1                              |   1,1     1,2     1,3     1,4
       while col <= 4:                      |
           print(f"{row},{col}, end=" ")    |   2,1     2,2,    2,3     2,4
           col += 1                         |
       print()                              |   3,1     3,2     3,3     3,4
       row += 1                             |


   For loops:
    + same idea, one loop for rows, one loop for columns

   for row in range (1, 4):           # 1 to 3
       for col in range (1, 5)        # 1 to 4
           print(f"{row},{col}, end=" ")
       print()

.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: Break and Continue

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Break
    Notes:
        + break instantly stops the loop you're currently in (jumps out of it)
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    nums = [2, 4, 7, 8]     | Output:
    for n in nums:          |
       if n == 7:           |   2
          break             |   4
       print(n)             |

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Continue
    Notes:
        + skips the rest of the current loop iteration and jumps to the next one.
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    num = [2, 4, 7, 8]      | Output:
    for n in nums:          |
       if n == 7:           |   2
           continue         |   4
       print(n)             |   8

.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: Loop else

    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
    Notes:
        + A loop may include an else clause that executes only if the loop terminates normally
          and doesn't use a break statement.
    -----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

While loop else:                                        | For loop else:
                                                        |
    while expression:                                   | for name in iterable:
        | Loop body |                                   |      | Loop body |
        | Expression evaluated to True |                |      | Execute for each item in iterable |
    else:                                               | else:
        | else body: sub-statements execute once |      |      | else body |
        | Expression evaluated to False |               |      | once when loop completes |

.......................................................................................................................

TOPIC: Getting both index and value when looping: enumerate()               | Output:
                                                                            |   Element 0: 4
1.     Using range() and len() to iterate over a sequence                   |   Element 1: 8
                                                                            |   Element 2: 10
        origins = [4, 8, 10]                                                -------------------------------------
        for index in range(len(origins)):
            value = origins[index]  # Retrieve value of element in list.
            print(f"Element {index}: {value}")

2.     Using list.index() to find the index of each element

        for value in origins:
            index = origins.index(value)  # Retrieve index of value in list
            print(f"Element {index}: {value}")

3.      ENUMERATE() FUNCTION

         for (index, value) in enumerate(origins):
            print(f"Element {index}: {value}")

        + enumerate function retrieves both index and corresponding element value at the same time,
          providing a cleaner and more readable solution.


